# Comma — AI developer rules

The rules for this repository are maintained in ONE file, so every agent and every human is
held to the same contract. Read it before changing anything:

    ./AGENTS.md

Do not copy rules back into this file. This file was a separate copy once and went stale: it
mandated appending to a log at `docs/system_log.md` (which does not exist — the file is at
`app/docs/system_log.md`) and described Comma as "100% cloudless" long after Google Drive
sync shipped. One file, one truth.

The short version:

1. Comma is TWO apps sharing ONE vault — the phone app (`src/`, `app/`) and the web PWA
   (`web/src/`). They read and write each other's files, and nothing checks that they agree
   at compile time. If you change sync, database schema, the crypto envelope, or the country
   registry, you MUST handle the twin file in the other app. See AGENTS.md §1.
2. Version numbers come from `node scripts/version.mjs`. Never hand-edit them.
3. Every user-visible change gets a CHANGELOG.md entry in the same commit. That file is
   published as the /changelog page on the docs site.
4. No `any` types. All DB aggregation happens inside SQLite via Drizzle — never `.reduce()`
   or `.filter()` over rows pulled into JS.
5. Build only what was asked. No speculative stubs or boilerplate for future screens.
